<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4322521>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 4. Morphological differentiation between Uroplatus fangorn sp. nov., U. fivehy sp. nov., and their closest relative, U. finiavana. The upper panel shows boxplots (median, quartiles, minimum/maximum and outliers) for selected meristic and morphometric variables and ratios; asterisks mark comparisons between U. fivehy and U. finiavana that were significant in Mann-Whitney U tests (* P <0.05; ** P <0.01). No statistical comparisons were performed for U. fangorn due to low sample size (N = 3). For original values of measurements, see Table 1. The lower panel shows intact (not regenerated) tails of individuals of the three species, illustrating differences in size and shape between species and sexes (all tails from males except where indicated as females)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4322521/files/figure.png" .

